The no-overlap predicate requires that at least one of the four separating conditions holds: left of , left of , below , or below . Constraint (1) enforces in-sheet placement, while constraint (2) activates non-overlap only for pairs on the same sheet.
When for every type, the problem recovers 2D-BPP exactly. A modest 10-type instance with average demand 5 generates copies, yielding potential overlap pairs per sheet.
